Name: copilot
Description: 👩‍✈️ Launch and manage containerized applications on AWS

Arguments.Name: init
Arguments.Description: Create a new ECS or App Runner application

Arguments.Description: Deploy your service or job to a "test" environment

Arguments.Description: The location of an existing Docker image

Arguments.Name: --name
Arguments.Description: Name of the service or job

Arguments.Name: --port
Arguments.Description: The port on which your service listens

Arguments.Name: --retries
Arguments.Description: Optional. The number of times to try restarting the job on a failure

Arguments.Name: --schedule
Arguments.Description: The schedule on which to run this job.  Accepts cron expressions of the format (M H DoM M DoW) and schedule definition strings.  For example: "0 * * * *", "@daily", "@weekly", "@every 1h30m". AWS Schedule Expressions of the form "rate(10 minutes)" or "cron(0 12 L * ? 2021)" are also accepted

Arguments.Name: --timeout
Arguments.Description: Optional. The total execution time for the task, including retries. Accepts valid Go duration strings. For example: "2h", "1h30m", "900s"

Arguments.Name: --type
Arguments.Description: Type of job or svc to create

Arguments.Description: Commands for applications. Applications are a collection of services and environments

Arguments.Description: Optional. Your existing custom domain name
